Crypto ATMs in India 
1. What is a Crypto ATM?
A Crypto ATM is a kiosk that allows users to buy (and sometimes sell) cryptocurrencies using cash or card.
It connects the user‚Äôs wallet to a crypto exchange or operator platform.

2. When Did Crypto ATMs Start in India?
India‚Äôs first Crypto ATM was launched in October 2018
Installed by Unocoin
Location: Kemp Fort Mall, Bengaluru
Purpose: Allowed users to buy and sell Bitcoin linked to Unocoin wallets
‚ö†Ô∏è This ATM was shut down later due to regulatory uncertainty.

3. Current Number of Crypto ATMs in India (Latest)
As per latest available aggregated listings (2024‚Äì2025):
üëâ Around 180+ crypto ATMs are reported across India
These listings come from global ATM aggregators and datasets
Important:
India does not have official RBI approval for crypto ATMs
Many machines operate in a regulatory grey area or are listed but not actively used
‚ÄúIndia has a limited and unclear presence of crypto ATMs, with around 180 reported machines as per global listings, but no official regulatory approval.‚Äù

